<topic id="xslt-syntax-highlight">
  <title>Syntax Highlighting in XSLT</title>
  <prolog>
    <metadata>
      <keywords>
        <indexterm>XSLT<indexterm>Syntax highlighting</indexterm></indexterm>
      </keywords>
    </metadata>
  </prolog>
  <body>
    <p conkeyref="reusables-editing-documents/syntax-highlight-p" id="p_m51_cgk_54b"/>
    <p id="p_n51_cgk_54b">To customize the colors or styles used for the syntax highlighting colors for XSLT files,
      follow these steps:<ol id="ol_o51_cgk_54b">
        <li id="li_p51_cgk_54b" irina="irina"><ph conkeyref="reusables-preferences-pages/Open-the-preferences-page"/>.</li>
        <li id="li_q51_cgk_54b" irina="irina">Go to <xref href="preferences-colors-sh.dita#preferences-colors-sh"><menucascade>
              <uicontrol>Editor</uicontrol>
              <uicontrol>Syntax Highlight</uicontrol>
            </menucascade></xref>.</li>
        <li id="li_r51_cgk_54b" irina="irina">Select and expand the <uicontrol>XML</uicontrol> section in the top pane.</li>
        <li id="li_s51_cgk_54b" irina="irina">Select the component you want to change and customize the colors or styles using the
          selectors to the right of the pane.</li>
        <li id="li_t51_cgk_54b" irina="irina">Select the <uicontrol>XSL</uicontrol> tab in the <uicontrol>Preview</uicontrol> pane to
          see the effects of your changes.</li>
      </ol></p>
    <note type="tip" id="note_u51_cgk_54b"><ph keyref="product"/> also allows you to specify syntax highlighting colors
      for specific XML elements and attributes with specific namespace prefixes. This can be done in
      the <xref
        href="preferences-colors-elements-by-prefix.dita#preferences-colors-elements-by-prefix"><menucascade>
          <uicontrol>Editor</uicontrol>
          <uicontrol>Syntax Highlight</uicontrol>
          <uicontrol>Elements/Attributes by Prefix</uicontrol>
        </menucascade> preferences page</xref>.</note>
  </body>
